<paragraph id="8BE1E215AE7DFF9DFF7EFAA13CD580D3" blockId="35.[151,999,1357,1412]" box="[151,937,1389,1412]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B92A3E07AE7DFF9DFF7EFAA13E5980D3" box="[151,293,1389,1412]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<typeStatus id="54E55CB7AE7DFF9DFF7EFAA13FB580D3" box="[151,201,1389,1412]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Type</typeStatus>
species:
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5E9996AE7DFF9DFEC5FAA13D3980D3" authority="Savigny" authorityName="Savigny" authorityYear="1822" box="[300,581,1389,1412]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Terebella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="medusa">
<emphasis id="B92A3E07AE7DFF9DFEC5FAA13E9A80D3" box="[300,486,1389,1412]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Terebella medusa</emphasis>
Savigny
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B92A3E07AE7DFF9DFDA2FAA13D1C80D3" box="[587,608,1389,1412]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">in</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9FE4AE7DFF9DFD8EFAA13C7680D3" author="Lamarck, J." box="[615,778,1389,1412]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref62867" refString="Lamarck, J. (1818) Annelids. Histoire naturelle des animaux sans vertebres. No. 2, 618 pp." type="book" year="1818">Lamarck, 1818</bibRefCitation>
, by monotypy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1E215AE7DFF9DFF7EFA793EBC8260" blockId="35.[151,1436,1461,2007]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B92A3E07AE7DFF9DFF7EFA793E648099" box="[151,280,1461,1486]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Branchiae on segments 2–4; eyespots present or absent; lateral lappets on segments 1 and 3 (rarely 1, 3 and 4); ventral shields from segment 2 or 3; pairs of nephridial papillae on segments 3–4 and 6–8; 17 pairs of notopodia from segment 4; chaetae bilimbate, with smooth tips; neuropodia from segment 5, uncini with single vertical series of teeth; uncini in single rows on segments 5–10; uncini in double separated rows, arranged back to back, until segment 20; thereafter uncini in single rows; pygidium sometimes with anal cirri. 
<emphasis id="B92A3E07AE7DFF9DFF7EF9B13E7B83C1" box="[151,263,1661,1686]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9FE4AE7DFF9DFEF8F9B13EBA83C0" author="Holthe, T." box="[273,454,1661,1687]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 236" refId="ref62170" refString="Holthe, T. (1986 b) Evolution, Systematics, and Distribution of the Polychaeta Terebellomorpha, with a catalogue of the taxa and a bibliography. Gunneria, 55, 1 - 236." type="journal article" year="1986">Holthe (1986b)</bibRefCitation>
recognized 15 valid species but from those described from the Grand 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E9996AE7DFF9DFAF5F9B13AEB83C0" authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[1308,1431,1661,1687]" genus="Caribbean" pageId="35" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Caribbean</taxonomicName>
, none are apparently valid. Thus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E9996AE7DFF9DFDFEF9693C1B83E8" authority="Verrill, 1900" authorityName=", Verrill" authorityYear="1900" box="[535,871,1701,1727]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Loimia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bermudensis">
<emphasis id="B92A3E07AE7DFF9DFDFEF9693DB683E9" box="[535,714,1701,1726]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">L. bermudensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9FE4AE7DFF9DFD38F9693C1B83E8" author="Verrill, A. E." box="[721,871,1701,1727]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="595 - 671" refId="ref64919" refString="Verrill, A. E. (1900) Additions to the Turbellaria, Nemertina, and Annelida of the Bermudas, with a revision of the New England genera and species. Transactions of the Connecticut Academy of Arts and Sciences, 10, 595 - 671." type="journal article" year="1900">Verrill, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry id="F349A285AE7DFF9DFC5AF9693B5D83E8" box="[947,1057,1701,1727]" name="Bermuda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Bermuda</collectingCountry>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E9996AE7DFF9DFBB7F9693AEB83E8" authority="Treadwell, 1929" authorityName=", Treadwell" authorityYear="1929" box="[1118,1431,1701,1727]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Loimia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis id="B92A3E07AE7DFF9DFBB7F9693BB283E9" box="[1118,1230,1701,1726]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">L. minuta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9FE4AE7DFF9DFB3FF9693AEB83E8" author="Treadwell, A. L." box="[1238,1431,1701,1727]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref64749" refString="Treadwell, A. L. (1929) New species of polychaetous annelids in the collections of the American Museum of Natural History, from Porto Rico, Florida, Lower California, and British Somaliland. American Museum Novitates of New York, 392, 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="1929">Treadwell, 1929</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from Florida, have been synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E9996AE7DFF9DFD7CF9013C7183B1" authorityName="Savigny" authorityYear="1822" box="[661,781,1741,1766]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Terebella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="medusa">
<emphasis id="B92A3E07AE7DFF9DFD7CF9013C7183B1" box="[661,781,1741,1766]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">L. medusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Savigny 
<emphasis id="B92A3E07AE7DFF9DFC6CF9013CE083B1" box="[901,924,1741,1766]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">in</emphasis>
Lamarck, 1822). However, based on examination of their 
<typeStatus id="54E55CB7AE7DFF9DFEBAF9393EF98258" box="[339,389,1781,1807]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">type</typeStatus>
specimens, both are regarded as distinct taxa; one has been already reinstated, and the other is herein reinstated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1E215AE7DFF9DFF2FF8893EF98280" blockId="35.[151,1436,1461,2007]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Two other species have been described from the North Atlantic Ocean: 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E9996AE7DFF9DFBE6F8893A2A8208" authority="Moore, 1903" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1903" box="[1039,1366,1861,1887]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Loimia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B92A3E07AE7DFF9DFBE6F8893BC98209" box="[1039,1205,1861,1886]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Loimia viridis</emphasis>
Moore, 1903
</taxonomicName>
, from Woods Hole, 
<collectingRegion id="499A2CF7AE7DFF9DFED0F8A13E9982D0" box="[313,485,1901,1927]" country="United States of America" name="Massachusetts" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Massachusetts</collectingRegion>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E9996AE7DFF9DFDCDF8A13C2482D0" authority="Andrews, 1892" authorityName="Andrews" authorityYear="1892" box="[548,856,1901,1927]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Loimia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="turgida">
<emphasis id="B92A3E07AE7DFF9DFDCDF8A13DE582D1" box="[548,665,1901,1926]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">L. turgida</emphasis>
Andrews, 1892
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingRegion id="499A2CF7AE7DFF9DFC4EF8A13B2182D0" box="[935,1117,1901,1927]" country="United States of America" name="North Carolina" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">North Carolina</collectingRegion>
; both are regarded as valid species. Recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9FE4AE7DFF9DFE9FF8593C1D82F8" author="Londono-Mesa, M. H. &amp; Carrera-Parra, L. F." box="[374,865,1941,1967]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 44" refId="ref63133" refString="Londono-Mesa, M. H. &amp; Carrera-Parra, L. F. (2005) Terebellidae (Polychaeta) from the Mexican Caribbean with description of four new species. Zootaxa, 1057, 1 - 44." type="journal article" year="2005">Londoño-Mesa and Carrera-Parra (2005)</bibRefCitation>
described a new species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E9996AE7DFF9DFB48F8593A5E82F9" authorityName="Londono-Mesa &amp; Carrera-Parra" authorityYear="2005" box="[1185,1314,1941,1966]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Loimia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="salazari">
<emphasis id="B92A3E07AE7DFF9DFB48F8593A5E82F9" box="[1185,1314,1941,1966]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">L. salazari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from the Mexican 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E9996AE7DFF9DFEEDF8713EFC8280" authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[260,384,1981,2007]" genus="Caribbean" pageId="35" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Caribbean</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C344B19EAE7AFF9AFF2FFF543F9F842D" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BE1E215AE7AFF9AFF2FFF543F9F842D" blockId="36.[151,1436,152,378]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Since 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E9996AE7AFF9AFEE6FF543EFB85E6" authorityName="Savigny" authorityYear="1822" box="[271,391,152,177]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Terebella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="medusa">
<emphasis id="B92A3E07AE7AFF9AFEE6FF543EFB85E6" box="[271,391,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">L. medusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered having a wide distribution, it has been identified in the Grand 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E9996AE7AFF9AFACAFF543AE785E5" authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[1315,1435,152,178]" genus="Caribbean" pageId="36" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Caribbean</taxonomicName>
region in many reports (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9FE4AE7AFF9AFE29FF0C3DBA858D" author="Salazar-Vallejo, S. I." box="[448,710,192,218]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="11 - 50" refId="ref64128" refString="Salazar-Vallejo, S. I. (1996) Lista de especies y bibliografia de poliquetos (Polychaeta) del Gran Caribe. Anales del Instituto de Biologia, Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Serie Zoologia, 67, 11 - 50." type="journal article" year="1996">Salazar-Vallejo, 1996</bibRefCitation>
). Nevertheless, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9FE4AE7AFF9AFC61FF0C3B92858D" author="Hutchings, P. A. &amp; Glasby, C. J." box="[904,1262,192,218]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="149 - 155" refId="ref62622" refString="Hutchings, P. A. &amp; Glasby, C. J. (1995) Description of the widely reported terebellid polychaetes Loimia medusa (Savigny) and Amphitrite rubra (Risso). Mitteilungen der Zooologisches Staatinstitut und zoologisches Museum, Hamburg, 92, 149 - 155." type="journal article" year="1995">Hutchings and Glasby (1995)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that such worldwide distribution is doubtful, and described a new species for the Australian records previously identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E9996AE7AFF9AFED9FEDC3ED5847E" authorityName="Savigny" authorityYear="1822" box="[304,425,272,297]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Terebella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="medusa">
<emphasis id="B92A3E07AE7AFF9AFED9FEDC3ED5847E" box="[304,425,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">L. medusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A current study is being done to evaluate the wide distribution of this species in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E9996AE7AFF9AFF7EFEF43E6F8405" authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[151,275,312,338]" genus="Caribbean" pageId="36" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Caribbean</taxonomicName>
. All these differences about 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E9996AE7AFF9AFD9DFEF43C5B8405" box="[628,807,312,338]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Loimia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B92A3E07AE7AFF9AFD9DFEF43DBB8406" box="[628,711,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Loimia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
will appear in a forthcoming world revision of the genus.
</paragraph>
